==English==

===Verb===
{{conj|applaud|applauds|applauded|applauded|applauding}}
'''to applaud'''  (''transitive'' and ''intransitive'')
# To [[express]] [[approval]] (of something) by [[clap|clapping]] the [[hand]]s.
#:''After the performance, the audience '''applauded''' for five minutes''
# To [[praise]], or express approval for something or someone.
#:''Although we don't like your methods, we '''applaud''' your motives.''

